thread.title: Prep Volleyball: Helias claims tourney crown
thread.title_full: Prep Volleyball: Helias claims tourney crown

author: News Tribune
title: Prep Volleyball: Helias claims tourney crown
text:
Share 
FESTUS — The Helias varsity volleyball team went 4-0-1 to capture the championship of the 32nd Annual Biehle Invitational Volleyball Tournament on Saturday at Festus High School. 
In pool play, the Lady Crusaders split with Northwest: Cedar Hill (25-16, 18-25) before defeating Sullivan (25-7, 25-13) and Hillsboro (25-20, 25-16). 
Helias finished first in its pool, earning a bye in the first round of the tournament. Then in the semifinals, Helias beat Hillsboro in a rematch, winning 25-9, 25-14. 
The Lady Crusaders then gained a measure of revenge for their earlier split by ripping Northwest: Cedar Hill 25-15, 25-12 in the championship match. 
For the tournament, Ashley Dudenhoeffer had 75 assists, 39 digs and 20 service points, while Suzie Kuensting had 26 service points, 18 kills and seven blocks. 
Also for Helias, Ellie Rockers had 26 kills and eight blocks, Hannah Borchelt had 28 kills and five blocks, Blake Berhorst led the defense with 52 digs, Maddie Dunkmann contributed 28 service points with eight aces and Clarissa Fennessey chipped in with 20 digs and 17 service points. 
The Lady Crusaders are now 26-3-1 and will play Thursday at Jefferson City. ﻿
